<p>The pins-and-string construction of an ellipsoid is a transfer of the id=
ea constructing an ellipse using two <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Ellipse#Pins-and-string_method" title=3D"Ellipse">pins and a string</a> =
(see diagram).
</p><p>A pins-and-string construction of an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Ellipsoid_of_revolution" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Ellipsoid=
 of revolution">ellipsoid of revolution</a> is given by the pins-and-string=
 construction of the rotated ellipse.=20
</p><p>The construction of points of a <i>triaxial ellipsoid</i> is more co=
mplicated. First ideas are due to the Scottish physicist <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Clerk_Maxwell" title=3D"James Clerk Maxwell">J=
. C. Maxwell</a> (1868).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipsoid#cite_note-9"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Main in=
vestigations and the extension to quadrics was done by the German mathemati=
cian O. Staude in 1882, 1886 and 1898.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-10" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipsoid#cite_note-10"><sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></=
a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipsoid#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-12=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipsoid#ci=
te_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> A description of the pins-and-string construction o=
f ellipsoids and hyperboloids is contained in the book <i><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geometry_and_the_Imagination" title=3D"Geometry and=
 the Imagination">Geometry and the Imagination</a></i> by <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Hilbert" title=3D"David Hilbert">Hilbert</a> =
&amp; <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stefan_Cohn-Vossen" title=3D=
"Stefan Cohn-Vossen">Cohn-Vossen</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-13" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipsoid#cite_note-13"><spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a=
></sup>
</p>
