<p>The ellipsoidal shape finds many practical applications:
</p>
<dl><dt><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geodesy" title=3D"Geodesy"=
>Geodesy</a></dt></dl>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth_ellipsoid" title=3D"=
Earth ellipsoid">Earth ellipsoid</a>, a mathematical figure approximating t=
he shape of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Earth" title=3D"Ea=
rth">Earth</a>.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reference_ellipsoid" class=3D"=
mw-redirect" title=3D"Reference ellipsoid">Reference ellipsoid</a>, a mathe=
matical figure approximating the shape of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Planetary_body" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Planetary body">plan=
etary bodies</a> in general.</li></ul>
<dl><dt><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mechanics" title=3D"Mechan=
ics">Mechanics</a></dt></dl>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poinsot%27s_ellipsoid" tit=
le=3D"Poinsot's ellipsoid">Poinsot's ellipsoid</a>, a geometrical method fo=
r visualizing the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torque-free_prec=
ession" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Torque-free precession">torque-free =
motion</a> of a rotating <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rigid_bod=
y" title=3D"Rigid body">rigid body</a>.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lam%C3%A9%27s_stress_ellipsoid=
" title=3D"Lam=C3=A9's stress ellipsoid">Lam=C3=A9's stress ellipsoid</a>, =
an alternative to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mohr%27s_circle"=
 title=3D"Mohr's circle">Mohr's circle</a> for the graphical representation=
 of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stress_(mechanics)" title=
=3D"Stress (mechanics)">stress</a> state at a point.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manipulability_ellipsoid" titl=
e=3D"Manipulability ellipsoid">Manipulability ellipsoid</a>, used to descri=
be a robot's freedom of motion.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacobi_ellipsoid" title=3D"Jac=
obi ellipsoid">Jacobi ellipsoid</a>, a triaxial ellipsoid formed by a rotat=
ing fluid</li></ul>
<dl><dt><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crystallography" title=3D"=
Crystallography">Crystallography</a></dt></dl>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Index_ellipsoid" title=3D"=
Index ellipsoid">Index ellipsoid</a>, a diagram of an ellipsoid that depict=
s the orientation and relative magnitude of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Refractive_index" title=3D"Refractive index">refractive indices</=
